              <title>Project-like assessments encourage deep learning</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/173</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/173</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[If you want your assessment to reward deep learning (personal construction of meaning, flexible understanding, transformation of current conceptions etc) rather than surface learning, then you should be thinking of project-like assessment, according to Sonia Bartoluzzi and Peter Goodyear.

“Instead of the assessment being a test of how well the materials have been memorised, the materials become a resource for the assessment project.”

Follow the link for the full discussion in the TELL Pattern Book, pp. 25-26.

